metadata.name: Sunflowers Over Politics
metadata.description:
The first Art & Poetry collaboration between Laurence Fuller & Sabet, over a year in the making. Inspired by the aesthetics of David Hockney & Van Gogh after seeing the soup can protestors attack art in museums to promote political agendas “stop looking at art, focus on politics” ~ by spray-painting sunflowers over the Houses of Parliament we say “stop focusing on politics, look at art”

Art by Sabet @sabet
AI Animation, Music, Poetry & Performance by Laurence Fuller @laurencefuller
